    "update_policy": "Baseline changes require explicit rationale in commit message and must reference the benchmark run that justifies the new values. Use 'make bench-json > bench-results.json' to capture a new baseline run.",
    "tolerance_policy": "Each metric budget is set to baseline_value * headroom_multiplier. The multiplier accounts for CI runner variance, OS scheduling jitter, and measurement noise. Tighter multipliers are used for low-variance operations (e.g., timer_cancel) and looser for high-variance ones (e.g., timer_register).",
